disco che nasce provvisorio, traballante, che ad ogni strato si compatta, cerca direzioni, si isola. Un tentativo di espandere, una ricerca nel songwrting e nell\'arrangiamento, di far uscire le canzoni nate da un chitarra ad altri ambienti e altre atmosfere.”</font></font></font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0.49cm; margin-bottom: 0.49cm;\"><font face=\"Arial Unicode MS, sans-serif\"><font size=\"3\"><font size=\"2\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\"><font face=\"Arial, sans-serif\">											</font></font>Roger Keith</font></font></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Princesa in Studio: Giorgio Tempesta: chitarra, voce, basso, rumori, arrangiamenti<br />   		     Lorenzo Tomio: voci, chitarra, arrangiamenti, programmazione <br />   		     Simone Peraz: suoni di sintesi<br />   		     Gabriele Piazza: batteria<br /><br />Princesa live: 	Giorgio Tempesta: chitarra, voce</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">         		Andrea Rottin: chitarra, tamburino, glockenspiel, voce  </p>','2008-01-09','1','676','2','0');
INSERT INTO `album_order` VALUES ('33','9','Stop the wheel','The Preacher','15','MDCP069','preacher.jpg','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Data di uscita: Giugno 2008</span><br /><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Supporto: LP 33giri 12\"</span><br />Stoutmusic e Madcap Collective presentano l\'ultimo disco di Stop the Wheel.<br />','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Release date: June 2008</span><br /> <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Type: LP 33 12\"</span><br /> Stoutmusic and Madcap Collective present the last album of Stop the Wheel.<br /> <br />','Registrato all’Ectoplasmic Garden da Marco Fasolo, usando tecniche risalenti a svariati decenni fa, interamente in analogico ed in monofonia, perchè le canzoni, seppur moderne, richiedevano que!’approccio semplice e magico. <br /> Il Predicatore tenta di convertire la massa, fallendo presto nel suo intento. Il Predicatore muore, vittima di una mano gelosa, trovando finalmente la pace tanto cercata. Ad ascoltarla su disco, questa storia riporta ad altri tempi e mondi. A.P.&#268;echov. Un quintetto di ottoni inglesi.<br /> “Il Tamburo di Latta“. Gli Everly Brothers.<br /> Ospiti speciali nel disco sono Chiara Gelmini a!a voce, <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Vittorio Demarin</span> (Father Murphy, Gomma Workshop) agli archi, il <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Coupland Brass Quintet </span>(Manchester, UK) agli ottoni, ed il grande<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> Loren Chasse</span> (Jewe!ed Antler Collective, San Francisco) alle atmosfere e treatments su “Apparition of Midnight”.<br /> L’artwork è stato curato da <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Lapis Niger</span> (Uochi Toki, - <a href=\"javascript:void(0);/*1218017125117*/\">www.lapisniger.blogspot.com </a>).<br /> <br /> <br /> <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">credits:</span><br /> all songs by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Francesco candura (bmi)</span><br /> for lyrics, info ecc.: <a href=\"javascript:void(0);/*1218017046089*/\">http://www.myspace.com/stopthewheel</a><br /> produced by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">marco fasolo</span><br /> mixed by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">marco fasolo & stw</span><br /> mastered by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Francesco fabiano</span><br /> add. artistic/technical help: <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">massimo tunin, adriano cecchia, abba zabba,andrea garbo, paolo mongardi</span>','Registrato all’Ectoplasmic Garden da Marco Fasolo, usando tecniche risalenti a svariati decenni fa, interamente in analogico ed in monofonia, perchè le canzoni, seppur moderne, richiedevano que!’approccio semplice e magico. <br /> Il Predicatore tenta di convertire la massa, fallendo presto nel suo intento. Il Predicatore muore, vittima di una mano gelosa, trovando finalmente la pace tanto cercata. Ad ascoltarla su disco, questa storia riporta ad altri tempi e mondi. A.P.&#268;echov. Un quintetto di ottoni inglesi.<br /> “Il Tamburo di Latta“. Gli Everly Brothers.<br /> Ospiti speciali nel disco sono Chiara Gelmini a!a voce, <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Vittorio Demarin</span> (Father Murphy, Gomma Workshop) agli archi, il <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Coupland Brass Quintet </span>(Manchester, UK) agli ottoni, ed il grande<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> Loren Chasse</span> (Jewe!ed Antler Collective, San Francisco) alle atmosfere e treatments su “Apparition of Midnight”.<br /> L’artwork è stato curato da <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Lapis Niger</span> (Uochi Toki, - <a href=\"javascript:void(0);/*1218017125117*/\">www.lapisniger.blogspot.com </a>).<br /> <br /> <br /> <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">credits:</span><br /> all songs by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Francesco candura (bmi)</span><br /> for lyrics, info ecc.: <a href=\"javascript:void(0);/*1218017046089*/\">http://www.myspace.com/stopthewheel</a><br /> produced by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">marco fasolo</span><br /> mixed by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">marco fasolo & stw</span><br /> mastered by <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Francesco fabiano</span><br /> add. artistic/technical help: <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">massimo tunin, adriano cecchia, abba zabba,andrea garbo, paolo mongardi</span>','2008-06-01','3','87','0','0');
INSERT INTO `album_order` VALUES ('32','22','Gretel e Hansel','FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE','10','','coverGH.jpg','<p><strong>Data d\'uscita: sabato 19 aprile 2008</strong></p>\r\n<p>Esce oggi, in occasione del quinto compleanno di <em>Madcap Collective</em>, <strong>FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE</strong>, il primo full lenght degli ultimi accolti nella famiglia Madcap: <strong><font size=\"3\">GRETEL e HANSEL</font></strong>!</p>','<p>It comes out today, april 19th, fifth Madcap anniversary, <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE</span>, first full lenght of <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">GRETEL e HANSEL</span>, the last project who joined our beloved <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Collective</span>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','<p align=\"center\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><em>Nel dare il benvenuto agli ultimi arrivati tra le proprie fila,</em></font></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><em>Madcap Collective è lieta di presentare</em>:</font> <br /> <br /> <br /></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><font size=\"4\" face=\"Tahoma\"><strong>Gretel e Hansel</strong> “FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE” MDCP066, CD 2008, 09 trks</font> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /></p>\r\n<p><a name=\"0.1_graphic02\"></a><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><strong></strong></font></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\"><strong>FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE</strong>:</font> <br /></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">La favola del porcospino e\' l\'escamotage stilistico su cui i <strong>Gretel e Hansel</strong> articolano il loro lavoro fatto di rimandi ad un certo codice letterario fiabesco, che si intrecciano con sonorità a tratti più pacate, ad altri più energiche, senza perdere coesione di fondo.</font></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">9 tracce in totale, 5 canzoni intervallate da 4 momenti parlati in cui e\' suddivisa la narrazione del racconto, interpretati da una voce femminile capace di ben amplificare le parole contenute nella storia. </font></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">Fin dalle prime note del pezzo di apertura omonimo del disco e\' chiaro che l\'intento dei 4 componenti del gruppo e\' quello di rapire l\'ascoltatore per portarlo in un mondo fatato, sospeso tra tinte di grigio e squarci di sole. <em>You know ?!? </em>e\' una sbirciata sotto il tendone di un circo itinerante, mentre <em>I prefer melody</em>, forse la canzone dove la voce si fa più rarefatta, rimanda ad uno scenario un po\' retro e, nonostante l\'intro con un suono di dobro stonato, il pezzo cresce fino a sfociare in un arpeggio di chitarra che sembra arrivare direttamente dalla quinta dimensione dei primi Byrds. <em>Duck in the mirror</em> e\' un pezzo giocato su suoni percussivi non tradizionali e continue discese cromatiche che aprono in un ritornello molto orecchiabile e chiudono con una piccola suite di free-folk di quasi sapore Zappiano. </font></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">Come per il nome della band, come per la storia stampata sulla superficie esterna del digipack, così anche il disco chiude al contrario delle aspettative con il pezzo forse piu\' incisivo del disco: <em>Sad Kids</em>, una marcetta di soldatini rotti che avanza inesorabile col suo piccolo esercito di suoni. La presenza di cori di bambini di chiara provenienza anglosassone, come d’altronde la lingua usata per il narrare la favola, regala una sferzata di vitalità e movimento all\'intero disco,  e concretizza il percorso della band, che sul finire dell’album cerca di affermare maggiormente un  suono più distintivo,  meno contaminato da rimandi e ispirazioni.</font></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE e\' una piccola opera travestita da favola che in una mezz\'ora scarsa e\' capace di catapultare l\'ascoltatore in un mondo distorto, una favola da cui e\' difficile uscire, piu\' che un disco un vero e proprio concept che si dichiara a partire dall\'artwork.</font> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">Per ulteriori informazioni, contatti, interviste o proposte,  preghiamo di contattare direttamente Frederico f.</font></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">Email: </font><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:federico@maledetto.it\"><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\" color=\"#0000ff\">federico@maledetto.it</font></a></p>\r\n<p><font size=\"2\" face=\"Tahoma\">Ph.    +39 339 7366471</font></p>','<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Madcap Collective is happy to present</span><br /></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><font size=\"4\" face=\"Tahoma\"><strong>Gretel e Hansel</strong> “FOLLOW THE PORCUPINE” MDCP066, CD 2008, 09 trks</font> <br style=\"font-weight: bold;\" /></div>\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: bold;\" /><br style=\"font-style: italic;\" /><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Gretel e Hansel</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\'</span>s<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> Follow the porcupine</span> is an incredible fairytale full of music and atmosphere. The first track is the opening of the whole story and from the beginning is clear that the band wanta to introduce the listener to a fabulous world. <br />The tale goes on with the telling voice able to give dramatic colours and at the same time vitality to the narration; the voice plays with the music and creates beautifull landscapes. <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">You Know?!?</span>  seems performed by a crazy circus, <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">I prefer Melody</span> is maybe the quitest song of the whole record, whith an untuned dobro and an electric guitar inspired by the early <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Byrds. Duck in the mirror</span> with his creazy drum and <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Sad Kids</span>, with the children vocals and a  mad broken army full of sounds, close the album too early not to play repeat. <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Follow the Porcupine</span> is a fairytale able to take the audiens in a suspended world.<br /><br />For any further informations, requests, interviews... please write to frederico f. federico@maledetto.it','2008-04-19','2','368','2','0');
INSERT INTO `album_order` VALUES ('34','18***20','Wolther goes Stranger','SO SAD','7','BA','sad.jpg','Ecco finalmente il DVD, realizzato e stampato da BLACK ARROW STUDIO AND PRESS; che documenta il tour americano di WOlther goes Stranger!','Here\'s finally SO SAD; a DVD who follows Wolther goes Stranger during his first US tour, realized and released by BLACK ARROW STUDIO and PRESS','<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><em>So Sad</em> è stato girato nell’ottobre del 2007, in occasione del breve tour USA di Wolther Goes Stranger. </font> </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">Per due settimane, Luca Mazzieri e Massimo Colucci non sono più Luca Mazzieri e Massimo Colucci ma Wolther. Dalle spiagge di Coney Island a downtown Baltimore, Wolther semplicemente <em>è</em>, per l’occhio della videocamera, per lo specchio, per gli spettatori. </font> </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">Wolther si trucca, balla, sussurra appiccicose parole d’amore, scandite dai battiti di una drum machine – accompagnati da sparse note di piano, da ronzii di trapano. Fin dal primo show, in un burlesque club dell’East Village, con strip girls che danzano sul palco, è evidente che quella di Wolther non è solo musica ma performance tout court. </font> </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">Luca e Massimo che passeggiano tra le case <em>cape code</em> della suburbia Americana (uno scenario che sembra uscito da Edward Scissorhands) sono un’apparizione: fantasmi/freaks, esseri improbabili – una delle realtà più originali e devianti del panorama musicale indipendente.</font></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><em>So Sad</em>, prodotto da Black Arrow Studio Press, è stato realizzato da Luca Dipierro e Rachel Bradley. Il DVD, in edizione limitata, sarà disponibile ai concerti di Wolther e sul sito di Madcap Collective, www.maledetto.it</font></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><br /> </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><br /> </p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">www.myspace.com/wolthergoesstranger</font></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">www.blackarrowpress.com</font></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">www.lucadipierro.com</font></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\">www.rachelbradley.net</font></p>','<p class=\"small\"><strong>SO SAD</strong><br />   (2007-2008, video) with Luca Mazzieri, Massimo Colucci, Clams Casino.<br /> Directed and edited by Luca Dipierro.</p>\r\n<p class=\"small\">From the burlesque clubs of the Village to Coney Island, a week in the life of Italian band Wolther Goes Stranger, touring the US for the first time.</p>','2008-08-01','0','74','4','4');
INSERT INTO `album_order` VALUES ('37','1***2***4***7***9***14***16***18***22***8***10***15***17***21','','Madcap VS Madcap','3','MDCP333','FrontCover.jpg','In occasione del quinto compleanno del Madcap Collective, abbiam\r\nrealizzato una compilation che potrebbe essere tranquillamente chiamata\r\n<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Madcap suona Madcap</span>. ','On the occasion of <strong>Madcap Collective</strong> fifth aniversary, we released a <em>Compilation</em> that could be easily called <em>Madcap plays Madcap</em>.','<strong>Tracklist:</strong><br>\r\n01. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=14\" target=\"_blank\">My Dear Killer</a> plays “Ceci”<br>\r\n(from <em>Wolther Goes Stranger</em> by Wolther Goes Stranger)<br>\r\n02. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=15\" target=\"_blank\">Pentolino’s Orchestra</a> plays “My Sweet, We’re Bright”<br>\r\n(from <em>We Don’t Need the Outisde</em> by Bob Corn)<br>\r\n03. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=16\" target=\"_blank\">Lorenzo Fragiacomo</a> plays “Fan”<br>\r\n(from <em>The Preacher</em> by Stop the Wheel)<br>\r\n04. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=9\" target=\"_blank\">Stop the Wheel</a> plays “Pijama O’ Rama”<br>\r\n(from <em>Cantina Tapes</em> by Gomma Workshop)<br>\r\n05. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=8\" target=\"_blank\">Gomma Workshop</a> plays “I’m not This Kind of Man”<br>\r\n(from <em>Perros</em> by Pentolino’s Orchestra)<br>\r\n06. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=1\" target=\"_blank\">Littlebrown</a> plays “Monster Munch”<br>\r\n(from <em>Big Saloon</em> by Beatrice Antolini)<br>\r\n07. <a href=\"http://www.blakeeee.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Blake/e/e/e</a> (ex <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=10\" target=\"_blank\">Franklin Delano</a>) plays “Window Pane”<br>\r\n(from <em>J.P.</em> by Princesa)<br>\r\n08. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=7\" target=\"_blank\">Princesa</a> plays “Some Guitars are Hard to Play”<br>\r\n(from <em>Father Murphy</em> by Father Murphy)<br>\r\n09. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=22\" target=\"_blank\">Gretel & Hansel</a> plays “(I Fear) Time”<br>\r\n(from <em>Clinical Shyness</em> by My Dear Killer)<br>\r\n10. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=18\" target=\"_blank\">Wolther Goes Stranger</a> plays “Call it a Day”<br>\r\n(from <em>Like a Smoking Gun in Front of Me</em> by Franklin Delano)<br>\r\n11. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=4\" target=\"_blank\">Father Murphy</a> plays “Liquid and Gaseos”<br>\r\n(from <span><em>Some (Flying) Kisses from a (Ground) Guitar</em> by Littlebrown)</span><br>\r\n12. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=21\" target=\"_blank\">Bob Corn</a> plays “I Prefer Melody”<br>\r\n(from <em>Follow the Porcupine</em> by Gretel & Hansel)<br>\r\n13. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=17\" target=\"_blank\">Beatrice Antolini</a> plays “Looking Glass”<br>\r\n(from <em>Songs About Nightmares</em> by Andrea Rottin)<br>\r\n14. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=2\" target=\"_blank\">Andrea Rottin</a> plays “Still Faces”<br>\r\n(from <em>When Ground Figures Bless in Black Tutus</em> by Lorenzo Fragiacomo)<br><br>***<br>In occasione del quinto compleanno del Madcap Collective, abbiam\r\nrealizzato una compilation che potrebbe essere tranquillamente chiamata\r\n<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">Madcap suona Madcap</span>. Abbiamo\r\nchiesto ai 14 diversi progetti solisti/band che in questi anni hanno\r\nlavorato con Madcap di eseguire e registrare una cover di una canzone\r\ndi un compagno di etichetta, canzone comunque presente in un disco\r\nprodotto dal Collettivo. Volendo fidarci della provvidenza, abbiam\r\nfatto gli abbinamenti grazie ad una democratica estrazione. Nel\r\ncompilare quindi la tracklist abbiam semplicemente seguito l\'ordine\r\nd\'estrazione dei diversi nomi. Ai progetti/band è stata lasciata\r\nlibertà massima nel scegliere il pezzo di cui appunto eseguire la\r\ncover, con la sola clausola di cui sopra.<br>Siam quindi qui\r\nfelicissimi nel presentare il risultato di questo che fondamentalmente\r\nè un regalo di compleanno che ci siamo autofatti, orgogliosi nel\r\nsottolineare quanto ogni partecipante abbia colto la giusta attitudine\r\nnel realizzare il proprio contributo.<br>Inizialmente stampata in 99 copie numerate, la compilation è adesso scaricabile qui per la cifra simbolica di 3 euro.<br>','<strong>Tracklist:</strong><br>\r\n01. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=14\" target=\"_blank\">My Dear Killer</a> plays “Ceci”<br>\r\n(from <em>Wolther Goes Stranger</em> by Wolther Goes Stranger)<br>\r\n02. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=15\" target=\"_blank\">Pentolino’s Orchestra</a> plays “My Sweet, We’re Bright”<br>\r\n(from <em>We Don’t Need the Outisde</em> by Bob Corn)<br>\r\n03. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=16\" target=\"_blank\">Lorenzo Fragiacomo</a> plays “Fan”<br>\r\n(from <em>The Preacher</em> by Stop the Wheel)<br>\r\n04. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=9\" target=\"_blank\">Stop the Wheel</a> plays “Pijama O’ Rama”<br>\r\n(from <em>Cantina Tapes</em> by Gomma Workshop)<br>\r\n05. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=8\" target=\"_blank\">Gomma Workshop</a> plays “I’m not This Kind of Man”<br>\r\n(from <em>Perros</em> by Pentolino’s Orchestra)<br>\r\n06. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=1\" target=\"_blank\">Littlebrown</a> plays “Monster Munch”<br>\r\n(from <em>Big Saloon</em> by Beatrice Antolini)<br>\r\n07. <a href=\"http://www.blakeeee.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Blake/e/e/e</a> (ex <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=10\" target=\"_blank\">Franklin Delano</a>) plays “Window Pane”<br>\r\n(from <em>J.P.</em> by Princesa)<br>\r\n08. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=7\" target=\"_blank\">Princesa</a> plays “Some Guitars are Hard to Play”<br>\r\n(from <em>Father Murphy</em> by Father Murphy)<br>\r\n09. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=22\" target=\"_blank\">Gretel & Hansel</a> plays “(I Fear) Time”<br>\r\n(from <em>Clinical Shyness</em> by My Dear Killer)<br>\r\n10. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=18\" target=\"_blank\">Wolther Goes Stranger</a> plays “Call it a Day”<br>\r\n(from <em>Like a Smoking Gun in Front of Me</em> by Franklin Delano)<br>\r\n11. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=4\" target=\"_blank\">Father Murphy</a> plays “Liquid and Gaseos”<br>\r\n(from <span><em>Some (Flying) Kisses from a (Ground) Guitar</em> by Littlebrown)</span><br>\r\n12. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=21\" target=\"_blank\">Bob Corn</a> plays “I Prefer Melody”<br>\r\n(from <em>Follow the Porcupine</em> by Gretel & Hansel)<br>\r\n13. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=17\" target=\"_blank\">Beatrice Antolini</a> plays “Looking Glass”<br>\r\n(from <em>Songs About Nightmares</em> by Andrea Rottin)<br>\r\n14. <a href=\"../artists.php?idArtist=2\" target=\"_blank\">Andrea Rottin</a> plays “Still Faces”<br>\r\n(from <em>When Ground Figures Bless in Black Tutus</em> by Lorenzo Fragiacomo)<br><br>***<br>\r\nOn the occasion of <strong>Madcap Collective</strong> fifth aniversary, we released a <em>Compilation</em> that could be easily called <em>Madcap plays Madcap</em>.\r\nThe Fourteen bands/projects/solo that worked during this year with\r\nMadcap have been asked to cover a song of another Madcap Artist\r\nreleased in these 5 years. Willing to trust to providence, we got the\r\nmatches thanks to a democratic kind of lottery draw. Ditto as above for\r\nthe track list.<br>\r\nAnd we’re really happy to say that every band caught the right attitude\r\nin joining this project, and the result is pretty amazing.<br>\r\nPrinted originally in only 99 copies, in a hand-assembled gatefold white sleeve, you can now download it for just three euros.<br><br>','2008-10-01','3','0','3','3');
INSERT INTO `album_order` VALUES ('36','4','','Do the sinister','10','BX002','sinister.jpg','Compilation di Father Murphy curata dall\'etichetta americana Box13','Father Murphys compilation released by the american label Box13','Title: DO THE SINISTER<br />Artist: FATHER MURPHY<br />Catalogue #: BX002<br />Label: BOX 13 (ROOSEVELT, NJ, US)<br />Format: CD<br />Tracks: 10<br />Tracklist: 1 We Know Who Our Enemies Are; 2 Millhouse; 3 I Was In A Coma, Then I Woke Up And Asked For A Strawberry Milkshake; 4 So Long; 5 Liquid Center; 6 Butterflies And Bats; 7 God Speed You My Nurse; 8 Drawn; 9 Three Musicians Getting Unknown<br /><br />tracks 1-3-4: previously released on “I saw seven horns risign from the Sea, when a rooster sang for the third time” 12\'\' Madcap Collective, 2006<br />tracks 2-6-7-9:  previously released on “Six musicians getting unknown” CD, Madcap Collective, 2005<br />track 5:  previously released on “S/t” CD, Madcap Collective 2003<br />Track 8:  previously released on “When we were young the world wasn\'t in your hands” CD, Madcap Collective, 2004<br />Ghost track: is there a ghost track? There\'s always a ghost track!<br /><br />Father Murphy “Do the Sinister” (Box 13) <br />Compliments to Michael Gira for pointing Dream Magazine in the direction of this intriguing Italian psychedelic outfit. Lumpy and smooth lurching uneven constructions suffused with oblique passions and simmering intensity. As the title aptly indicates there’s a vaguely sinister quality to the music these folks make. Even the lighter moments have a slightly uneasy nightmarish undertone to them, but in a completely natural and unforced way. A mix of male and female vocalists, loudness and subtlety, and a wide range of stylistic influences blended into something quite unique. Though they sing everything in English they have a distinctively Italian feeling. In a world of cookie-cutter imitators, it’s very refreshing to find something so disturbingly and provocatively unique. These folks also sent along a great CD-R of their upcoming album “...And He Told Us to Turn to the Sun” which is perhaps even more intense, edgy and fascinating than Do the Sinister. This is definitely a band to keep an eye and ear open for. <br />            George Parsons Dream Magazine 9  www.dreamgeo.com','Title: DO THE SINISTER<br />Artist: FATHER MURPHY<br />Catalogue #: BX002<br />Label: BOX 13 (ROOSEVELT, NJ, US)<br />Format: CD<br />Tracks: 10<br />Tracklist: 1 We Know Who Our Enemies Are; 2 Millhouse; 3 I Was In A Coma, Then I Woke Up And Asked For A Strawberry Milkshake; 4 So Long; 5 Liquid Center; 6 Butterflies And Bats; 7 God Speed You My Nurse; 8 Drawn; 9 Three Musicians Getting Unknown<br /><br />tracks 1-3-4: previously released on “I saw seven horns risign from the Sea, when a rooster sang for the third time” 12\'\' Madcap Collective, 2006<br />tracks 2-6-7-9:  previously released on “Six musicians getting unknown” CD, Madcap Collective, 2005<br />track 5:  previously released on “S/t” CD, Madcap Collective 2003<br />Track 8:  previously released on “When we were young the world wasn\'t in your hands” CD, Madcap Collective, 2004<br />Ghost track: is there a ghost track? There\'s always a ghost track!<br /><br />Father Murphy “Do the Sinister” (Box 13) <br />Compliments to Michael Gira for pointing Dream Magazine in the direction of this intriguing Italian psychedelic outfit. Lumpy and smooth lurching uneven constructions suffused with oblique passions and simmering intensity. As the title aptly indicates there’s a vaguely sinister quality to the music these folks make. Even the lighter moments have a slightly uneasy nightmarish undertone to them, but in a completely natural and unforced way. A mix of male and female vocalists, loudness and subtlety, and a wide range of stylistic influences blended into something quite unique. Though they sing everything in English they have a distinctively Italian feeling. In a world of cookie-cutter imitators, it’s very refreshing to find something so disturbingly and provocatively unique. These folks also sent along a great CD-R of their upcoming album “...And He Told Us to Turn to the Sun” which is perhaps even more intense, edgy and fascinating than Do the Sinister. This is definitely a band to keep an eye and ear open for. <br />            George Parsons Dream Magazine 9  www.dreamgeo.com','2008-07-01','2','12','2','3');